    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Biased Drug Research</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr Melvin H Kirschner letter says he fears for his patients when he reads that medications he prescribes are released for public use based on studies that may have been biased or dishonest research</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As a practicing physician, I was very disturbed by ''After Sanctions, Doctors Get Drug Company Pay'' (front page, June 3).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As a practicing physician, I was very disturbed by ''After Sanctions, Doctors Get Drug Company Pay'' (front page, June 3).</p>
        <p>When I prescribe a medication, I'm assuming that it has been carefully and honestly studied by both the manufacturers and the Food and Drug Administration before being released for general use, and that the reports of its benefits and risks have been accurately reported.</p>
        <p>I fear for my patients when I read that the medications I prescribe are released for public use based on studies that may have been biased or dishonest research.</p>
        <p>Melvin H. Kirschner, M.D.  Van Nuys, Calif., June 3, 2007</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
